<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-02-24T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-02-24T06:00:00-05:00" n="501" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d501">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24 Raw Materials/1518:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-02-24T12:00:00+01:00">February 24, 1941—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received February
                                    24—9:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>691. Both prior and subsequent to the receipt of the Department’s
                                552, February 20, the Embassy obtained informally assurances that
                                the 100% quota would be maintained. Since agreement to ensure the
                                maintenance of the quota seems to be sufficiently general, both
                                among the unofficial and official members of the British and Dutch
                                Governments, a prior meeting today could only have done more harm
                                than good. A luncheon would have been equally a tour de force since
                                a representative of the Embassy is lunching with the International
                                Committee after its meeting tomorrow.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>